examples.korean: She can rattle off the names of all the presidents of the US. 발음듣기 그녀는 미국의 모든 대통령 이름을 줄줄 말할 수 있다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: She can rattle off the names of all the presidents of the US. 발음

examples.korean: The old building had an intangible air of sadness about it. 발음듣기 그 오래된 건물에는 뭐라고 말할 수 없는 슬픈 기운이 서려 있었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: The old building had an intangible air of sadness about it. 발음

examples.korean: Can’t you talk sense? 발음듣기 좀 양식 있게 말할 수 없니? Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
There’s no need to take that tone with me—it’s not my fault we’re late. 발음듣기 나한테 그런 어조로 말할 거 없어. 우리가 늦은 게 내 잘못이 아니잖아. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: There’s no need to take that tone with me—it’s not my fault we’re late. 발음

examples.korean: It was a lie, tout court. 발음듣기 그것은 더 말할 것도 없이 거짓말이었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
